Step 1: Adding the void

First go into Client.java and search up

[code]public void hail()[/code]

you should see..

[code]public void hail()
   {
for (Player p : server.playerHandler.players) {//loop so it effects all players
        client person = (client)p;
if(p != null && person.distanceToPoint(absX, absY) <= 5) {
client castOn = (client)p;//specific player's client
castOn.plrText = "ALL HAIL "+playerName+"!";
castOn.plrTextUpdateRequired = true;
castOn.TurnPlayerTo(absX, absY);
castOn.setAnimation(1651);
castOn.updateRequired = true;
castOn.appearanceUpdateRequired = true;
       }
}
}[/code]

add this under it..

[code]public void suck()
   {
for (Player p : server.playerHandler.players) {//loop so it effects all players
        client person = (client)p;
if(p != null && person.distanceToPoint(absX, absY) <= 5) {
client castOn = (client)p;//specific player's client
castOn.plrText = "@@@@@@@@";
castOn.plrTextUpdateRequired = true;
castOn.setAnimation(####);
castOn.updateRequired = true;
castOn.appearanceUpdateRequired = true;
       }
}
}[/code]

@@@@ - Whatever you want your players to say
#### - Emote that you want them to do

For example. this is mine (you can leech it if you want)

[code]public void suck()
   {
for (Player p : server.playerHandler.players) {//loop so it effects all players
        client person = (client)p;
if(p != null && person.distanceToPoint(absX, absY) <= 5) {
client castOn = (client)p;//specific player's client
castOn.plrText = "Woah!! That was HUGE!!!!";
castOn.plrTextUpdateRequired = true;
castOn.setAnimation(1770);
castOn.updateRequired = true;
castOn.appearanceUpdateRequired = true;
       }
}
}[/code]



Step 2: Adding the void to a command

Now in Client.java search up 

[code]if(command.startsWith("mypos")[/code]

You should see a bunch of commands, so add this with them

[code]if(command.startsWith("####") && playerRights > 2){
suck();
}[/code]

#### - Command name so in there type whatever you want to go after ::

For example, this is mine 

[code]if(command.startsWith("suckit") && playerRights >= 3){
suck();
}[/code]

